title: ContextHelper: global Context variable restored
message:
ContextHelper: global Context variable restored

Skeleton was setup so that you could use anything without Context because
you had to extend SkeletonApplication which saved getApplicationContext()
as global Context -- which was valid.
Then I decided to move that logic away so that the library could be used
without extending SkeletonApplication and to prevent some possible
memory leaks.
Yet again, I restored the old logic, in a ContextHelper class. If
SkeletonApplication is not extended, ContextHelper.applicationContext(Context)
can still be manually called ; otherwise any Skeleton method requiring a
valid Context will throw a NullPointerException.
No memory leaks from the application's (global) Context.
